This cross section is a square with side length $f(x) = 5 - x.$  The area of this square is then $f(x)^2 = (5-x)^2.$  Thus, the volume of the solid is given by the integral \[\int_0^5 (5-x)^2\,dx.\]Expanding the integrand, we get \[\int_0^5 (25 - 10x + x^2)\,dx = \left[25x - 5x^2 + \frac{1}{3}x^3\right]_0^5 = \boxed{\frac{125}{3}}.\]

